    <string name="about_title">About</string>
    <string name="about_howtoplay_title">How to play</string>
    <string name="about_howtoplay_text">In Math Balls, the goal is to combine numbered balls to reach a target sum. All balls must be pressed down at the same time. Any number of balls can be combined.\n\nIf the red line at the top goes down, the game is over. It is reset each time the current target sum is reached.\n\nThe blue line at the top marks the way towards the next level. Each level will make the game harder.\n\nThere are three difficulty levels that can be set in the menu.</string>
    <string name="about_scoring_title">Scoring</string>
    <string name="about_scoring_text">Scoring points in Math Balls is based on the color of the balls and the number of balls combined to the target sum. Blue balls are worth most, then red balls and green balls are worth the least. The more balls that are combined at once, the higher score you get. It is often better to combine many green and red balls, compared to a few blue ones.</string>
